				<p rend="align(center)"><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Pa.</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(center)">Dear Sir</p>
				<p><sic>You</sic> favor came duly to hand<lb/> &#38; duly attended to<lb/>  The freight for the books<lb/> will be paid&#44; as soon as the<lb/> amount due to you for the<lb/> book will be sent the freight<lb/> will be included</p>
				<p>We had yesterday a great day<lb/> here&#44; the new <sic>jewish</sic> hospi&#758;<lb/>tal was dedicated&#44; <persName>Wise</persName><lb/> declined to be present <persName>Dr. Lili</persName>&#44;<lb/>put <sic>Spoke</sic> and exalted the<lb/> prosperity of Religion in<lb/> <placeName>Israel</placeName> which becomes daily more<lb/> and more the connection of the<lb/> heart&#44; for benevolence is the<lb/> only true Religion which<lb/> all the Prophets and sages</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>alluded to when <sic>the</sic> repre&#758;<lb/>manded the people for their<lb/> irreligious life.</p>
				<p>My <sic>Speech</sic> which I delivered<lb/> at the occasion I shall<lb/> send you as soon as it<lb/> will copied</p>
				<p>Hoping that these lines<lb/> will find you enjoying<lb/> the best health<lb/> I remain Sir most<lb/> Respectfully<lb/> Yours</p>
				<p><persName role="author">Dr <add>&#63;</add></persName></p>
